One time (I had fallen asleep in class) I dreamed that a fascist party had overtaken the government and installed all kinds of bizarre rules. All citizens were forced to only listen to classical music and compose pieces every day - they were executed if they refused to do this.
@0x49fa98

The dictator was not called a "Duce" or "Fuhrer" but "The Tchaikovsky". It was a title, not a name, whoever was in power was The Tchaikovsky. He could spy and secretly listen to all people, in their homes and at work, and reviewed all musical compositions that they produced.

His reigning place, his throne, was somewhere above the city, and it looked like a spiderweb, all phone lines led up there. Every day and night he sat, frenzied, listening to thousands of melodies and with 100s of music sheets, until he lost his mind, always listening, listening.
